    "(ii) These operators act on equivalent Hilbert spaces and are related by a unitary evolution operator S:b i = S † a i S, b † i = S † a † i S. (2.2)(iii) There exists a time-invariant vacuum which does not contain particles.",
    "That is,a i |0⟩ = b i |0⟩ = 0, S|0⟩ = |0⟩.",
    "(2.3)JHEP01( 2024)139(iv) One-particle states evolve trivially.",
    "In other words, they are stableb † i |0⟩ = S † a † i |0⟩ = a † i |0⟩.",
    "(2.4)In particular, this implies Sa † i |0⟩ = a † i |0⟩ thanks to the unitarity condition S † S = 1."
  ]
}